- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a neural embedding algorithm for learning distributed representations of nodes and networks simultaneously, which is a common topic in social and information networks research.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a neural network to learn the embeddings.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the scalability of the algorithm to real-world graphs with many nodes.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also possible as the paper proposes a new algorithm for embedding networks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses a machine learning approach to learn the embeddings.
